nodes.bodyText:
An empty list is only put into the topicMessagesQueue in the shutdown hook, which is used as a special value to gracefully complete the flux. btw, BlockingQueue by spec throws NPE if the element to add is null, so an empty list is chosen as the special value.
During normal processing, at the beginning of onSave, we have
if (!isEnabled() || topicMessages.isEmpty()) {
    return;
}

so only when there are messages, the list is pushed into the flux.

